  "result": "Hash tables handle collisions two main ways.\n\nChaining: each bucket holds linked list (or tree). Collisions append to list. O(1) avg, O(n) worst. Java `HashMap` uses this (upgrades list→red-black tree at 8 entries).\n\nOpen addressing: probe for next empty slot in same array. Variants: linear probing (next slot), quadratic (i² step), double hashing (second hash as step). Needs load factor <~0.7 and tombstones for deletes. Python `dict`, Go `map`, most modern impls use this — better cache locality.\n\nTrade-off: chaining tolerates high load + easy deletes; open addressing faster on cache, worse clustering.",
